    "body": "Adds the AutoDeploy trtllm_mla attention backend (wraps TRT-LLM thop.attention with is_mla_enable=True) for DeepSeek-style MLA models — plus the fused-RoPE transform, CUDA-graph infra, and FP8 KV cache\r\n  plumbing.\r\n\r\n  - Prefill via thop.attention(context_only); decode via mla_rope_generation preamble + thop.attention(generation_only); fuse_rope_into_trtllm_mla routes the model's cos/sin table through node meta →\r\n  get_attr node → cached op.\r\n  - Module-level planner with host/device prepare_metadata split; pre-allocated pinned host buffers; Triton ragged_to_block_table for paged block_offsets; per-layer C++ AttentionOp cache collapsed to two\r\n  entries (decode=0, prefill=1) so all layers share the same two cache slots.\r\n  - FP8 KV cache is opt-in via kv_cache_config.dtype: fp8 in deepseek-r1.yaml (no backend-side weight sniff). Fix: HFAutoDeployModelFactory.get_cache_config_updates used to default missing kv_cache_dtype to\r\n   \"auto\" and clobber explicit yaml values — now returns {} when the quant-config reader is silent.\r\n  - Accuracy refs for DeepSeek-R1-0528 updated with kv_cache_quant_algo=FP8.\r\n\r\n  Special handlings\r\n\r\n  - v_head_dim != qk_nope_head_dim hard guard — C++ context FMHA derives headSizeV from qk_nope_head_dim; mismatched models (GLM-4.7-Flash etc.) must use flashinfer_mla.\r\n  - mla_rope_generation is mandatory before decode thop.attention (cu_q/cu_kv, scheduler counter, FP8 Q-quant + BMM scales, paged cache write); no-fuse passes identity cos/sin so the kernel's RoPE is a\r\n  no-op. Prefill treats every seq as fresh (past_kv=0); thop's cached-KV context path would otherwise corrupt output.\r\n  - FP8 context FMHA reads V with a grouped-by-dim stride → kv_b_proj cached per-layer in that layout and V stays a non-contiguous view (do not clone). SM90 + FP8 KV cache routes decode through Flash MLA\r\n  with dedicated flash_mla_tile_scheduler_metadata / flash_mla_num_splits scratch.\r\n\r\n- Adds v_stride_in_bytes plumbing through EnqueueContextParams → MHARunnerParams → FusedMHARunnerV2::setupKernelParams, and populates it from v->strides()[0] * v->element_size() in thop/attentionOp.cpp.  Lets the MLA context FMHA handle contiguous V (AutoDeploy) and non-contiguous V from kv.split() (PyTorch backend) uniformly; previously the runner hardcoded the non-contiguous stride and crashed with\r\nillegal memory access on SM90 when V was contiguous.\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * TensorRT-LLM MLA attention backend and cached MLA attention ops exposed for AutoDeploy\n  * New graph transform to fuse RoPE into MLA decode; RoPE fusion toggle added to configs\n\n* **Improvements**\n  * Optional override for V-tensor stride to handle non-contiguous memory layouts\n  * FP8 KV-cache support and related config behavior refinements\n\n* **Tests**\n  * End-to-end MLA unit tests and added accuracy references for DeepSeek-R1 with FP8 KV cache\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease write the PR title by following this template:\r\n\r\n**[JIRA ticket/NVBugs ID/GitHub issue/None][type] Summary**\r\n\r\nValid ticket formats:\r\n  - JIRA ticket: [TRTLLM-1234] or [FOOBAR-123] for other FOOBAR project\r\n  - NVBugs ID: [https://nvbugs/1234567]\r\n  - GitHub issue: [#1234]\r\n  - No ticket: [None]\r\n\r\nValid types (lowercase): [fix], [feat], [doc], [infra], [chore], etc.\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n  - [TRTLLM-1234][feat] Add new feature\r\n  - [https://nvbugs/1234567][fix] Fix some bugs\r\n  - [#1234][doc] Update documentation\r\n  - [None][chore] Minor clean-up\r\n\r\nAlternative (faster) way using CodeRabbit AI:\r\n\r\n**[JIRA ticket/NVBugs ID/GitHub issue/None] @coderabbitai title**\r\n\r\nNOTE: \"@coderabbitai title\" will be replaced by the title generated by CodeRabbit AI, that includes the \"[type]\" and title.\r\nFor more info, see /.coderabbit.yaml.\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease explain the issue and the solution in short.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Test Coverage\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nPlease list clearly what are the relevant test(s) that can safeguard the changes in the PR. This helps us to ensure we have sufficient test coverage for the PR.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## PR Checklist\r\n\r\nPlease review the following before submitting your PR:\r\n- PR description clearly explains what and why. If using CodeRabbit's summary, please make sure it makes sense.\r\n- PR Follows [TRT-LLM CODING GUIDELINES](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/CODING_GUIDELINES.md) to the best of your knowledge.\r\n- Test cases are provided for new code paths (see [test instructions](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/tree/main/tests#1-how-does-the-ci-work))\r\n- Any new dependencies have been scanned for license and vulnerabilities\r\n- [CODEOWNERS](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) updated if ownership changes\r\n- Documentation updated as needed\r\n- Update [tava architecture diagram](https://github.com/NVIDIA/TensorRT-LLM/blob/main/.github/tava_architecture_diagram.md) if there is a significant design change in PR.\r\n- The reviewers assigned automatically/manually are appropriate for the PR.\r\n\r\n\r\n- [x] Please check this after reviewing the above items as appropriate for this PR.\r\n\r\n## GitHub Bot Help\r\n\r\nTo see a list of available CI bot commands, please comment `/bot help`.\r\n",
